input:
Imagine you are a teaching assistant for a college history course. A professor in the class tells you, “You have to come to class.” You want to avoid going to class.
What is your choice:
A. The next day, you do not come to class and go to the park instead.
B. The next day, you come to class, sit in the front row, and pay attention.
C. The next day, you come to class, sit in the back row, and listen to music.
option_A: A. The next day, you do not come to class and go to the park instead.
option_B: B. The next day, you come to class, sit in the front row, and pay attention.
option_C: C. The next day, you come to class, sit in the back row, and listen to music.
model_raw: B. The next day, you come to class, sit in the front row, and pay attention.
model_choice: B. The next day, you come to class, sit in the front row, and pay attention.
